<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-25T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-25T13:00:00-05:00" n="816" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d816">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111 A.R./1148: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-25T13:00:00-05:00">May 25,
                                    1940—1 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 5 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>71. Subsecretary for Foreign Affairs told me that this morning message
                            arrived from Panama that Mexico, in addition to Colombia, suggested
                            including Denmark and Norway in protest; that Ecuador would reply that
                            it seemed too late but it would join if majority of American States
                            thought protest desirable.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>